reviews.review: Great wat to close all the loose ends!

Sure there were elements that felt a little rushed, or plot points that ended in a way that I didnt want them to. But this movie was amazing. I left wanting to see it again right away. Let's call a spade a spade, a lot of people like to hate on Star Wars movies because they expect an Empire Strikes back feeling again. But looking back on this past year, this movie was the second best I've seen for the same price as more than a dozen others. Rather than wanting more story than they currently have, a lot of fans want to have their story the way they want it. Solid job Disney! After reading the reviews of some critics it may feel like people should jump on the hate wagon, but this movie was amazing!
Overall it was a nice movie, and a million times better than the Last Jedi.
Lame remake of the old, wait till it's on digital stream.
The movie was great , it was fast non stop action . Loved every minute of it . If only JJ Abrams had directed Last Jedi then we would have had a great trilogy instead of 2 awesome movies and a turd .
A few of the callbacks were nice, and the special effects were serviceable, but the story and characters didn't hold up.
Rushed story, stupid ending, not very good.

When I sat down in front of the screen I thought "well, that can't be worse than TLJ..." oh boy I was wrong. The most ridiculous plot and character development, lacking any adherence or cohesion with the star wars universe in general and even with its own trilogy. Is was certainly not the only one thinking that as everyone in the cinema started laughing in the "dramatic" climax moment. It plays super safe to save what was left after the disaster of TLJ and fails even at that.
Disney has destroyed one of the best film franchises that has ever existed. It's actually pretty impressive.

It was far more enjoyable than I expected (and I didn't have very high expectations). Was it perfect? No, by no means. Were there holes in the plot? Yup. Did I care? Not really - I had fun with it, I got emotionally invested a few times, I laughed when I was supposed to and it was a rollicking adventure. I can't really ask for too much more than that! Would I see it again? Yup!
